name: transmission network construction, electricity, high voltage direct current aerial line | transmission network, electricity, high voltage direct current aerial line | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/26172/documentation

This dataset represents the construction and decommissioning of 1 km transmission network high voltage direct current aerial line. The service life of the network was assumed to be 40 years. For this period also maintenance is considered as a service. Default value for power losses at 50 % load sum up to 2.14E8 kWh/km. Different from the literature source recycling was modelled according to the cut-off approach.;The inventory was modelled according to Jorge, R., Hawkins, T.R., Hertwich, E.G (2012): Life cycle assessment of electricity transmission and distribution - part 1: power lines and cables. Int J Life Cycle Assess 17: 9-15, supplementary material

The activity starts with cable and mast production according to material composition (energy requirements for cable and mast production not included). Maintenance is included as a service. Substations are not included.

This activity ends with the decommissioning of transition network according to material composition
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Time frame of the underlying literature sources
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The scope of the underlying literature source is Europe
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The voltage level is assumed to be 250 or 350 kV, respectively.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: LCI data on resource use and emissions for production of materials, installation, maintenance, and end of life were provided by the Danish utility company Energinet.dk. No data referring to line manufacturing (assembly of components) were available, and hence this process was not included.
